# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
The structure consists of 9 building blocks arranged in multiple layers:
- 3 orange cylindrical pillars
- 2 orange triangular roof pieces
- 1 red house-like structure with an arch
- 2 yellow semi-circular pieces
- 1 yellow rectangular beam

## Spatial Relationships
The structure appears to be a tower-like building with:
- Two orange cylindrical pillars as the base (at the bottom)
- A yellow rectangular beam connecting the two pillars horizontally
- A red house-like structure with an arch sitting on top of the beam
- Yellow semi-circular pieces inside the arched openings of the red structure
- A third orange cylindrical pillar extending upward from behind the red structure
- An orange triangular roof piece at the top of the tall pillar
- Another orange triangular roof piece on top of the red house structure

# Required Blocks from the Dictionary

Based on the target structure, I need the following blocks:
- Block 8 (orange cylinder) - used 3 times for the pillars
- Block 1 (red arched structure) - used 1 time
- Block 4 (yellow rectangular beam) - used 1 time
- Block 10 (yellow semi-circular piece) - used 2 times
- Block 15 (orange triangular roof) - used 1 time
- Block 16 (orange triangular roof) - used 1 time

# Assembly Order

```
{
   Step1: Move block with index 8
   Step2: Move block with index 8
   Step3: Move block with index 4
   Step4: Move block with index 1
   Step5: Move block with index 10
   Step6: Move block with index 10
   Step7: Move block with index 16
   Step8: Move block with index 8
   Step9: Move block with index 15
}
```

The assembly order starts with placing the two base pillars, then the connecting beam, followed by the red house structure with its semi-circular inserts and roof. Finally, the tall pillar is placed behind and its roof is added last.
